  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity-strengthening with organisations and communities affected by mining in Peru</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Red Muqui is a Peruvian network of NGO and civil society organisations working to promote human and environmental rights, the patrimony of campesino and indigenous populations and to support communities in regions affected by extractive mining. A number of present and former CAFOD partners form part of the Muqui network. This project, supported by a consortium of agencies seeks to strengthen the capacities of Muqui members and the communities they work with to increase mutual coordination and support, in order to defend their individual and collective rights. It also seeks to promote alternatives to extractive industries and to influence public agendas and policies from community to national and international levels to protect human rights defenders and protect environmental rights.</narrative>
  </description>
